<!DOCTYPE html>
<!--
    references:
    - images from: DLSU AU (Facebook Page) https://www.facebook.com/DLSUAU
    - https://www.w3schools.com/html/html_images.asp
    - https://www.freecodecamp.org/news/how-to-work-with-images-in-html/
    - https://codingartistweb.com/2024/12/image-gallery-with-lightbox-effect-using-html-css-and-javascript/
-->
<html>
    <head>
        <title>Archers for UNICEF (AU) | OrgSpace</title>
        <link rel="stylesheet" href="/style.css">
    </head>

    <body data-org="au@dlsu.edu.ph">
        <main>
            <nav id="menu">
                <span class="menu-title">DLSU Organizations</span>
                <input type="checkbox" id="responsive-menu"><label></label>
                <ul>
                    <li><a href="/">Home</a></li>
                    <li><a class="dropdown-arrow active" href="#organizations">Organizations</a>
                        <ul class="sub-menus">
                            <li><a href="/org1">Archers for UNICEF</a></li>
                            <li><a href="/org2">Council of Student Organizations</a></li>
                            <li><a href="/org3">Information Security Organization</a></li>
                            <li><a href="/org4">La Salle Computer Society</a></li>
                            <li><a href="/org5">Management of Financial Institutions Association</a></li>
                        </ul>
                    </li>
                    <li><a href="/contact">Contact Us</a></li>


                    <li class="menu-profile" id="profileMenu">
                        <button class="profile-btn" id="profileBtn" aria-haspopup="true" aria-expanded="false">
                        <img src="/assets/profile-icon.png" alt="Account" class="profile-icon">
                        </button>

                        <ul class="profile-dropdown" id="profileDropdown" role="menu" aria-label="Account menu"></ul>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </nav>

            <section class="org-header">
                <div class="org-header-inner">
                    <img src="/assets/AU_logo1.png" alt="Archers for UNICEF Logo" class="org-logo">

                    <div class="org-header-text">
                        <h1>Archers for UNICEF (AU)</h1>
                        <p class="org-tagline">
                            Always for the women and children.
                        </p>
                        <span class="org-category">Volunteer Organization</span>

                        <a href="/reviews1" class="reviews-btn">See Reviews</a>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </section>

            <section class="org-body">
                
                <div class="org-highlights">
                    <img src="/assets/AU1.jpg" alt="AU Highlight 1" class="lightbox-trigger">
                    <img src="/assets/AU2.jpg" alt="AU Highlight 2" class="lightbox-trigger">
                    <img src="/assets/AU3.jpg" alt="AU Highlight 3" class="lightbox-trigger">
                </div>

                <div class="org-split">
                    <div class="org-main">

                        <div class="org-section">
                            <h2>About the Organization</h2>
                            <p>
                                Archers for UNICEF of De La Salle University-Manila is a non-profit organization that envisions a brighter 
                                and more inclusive future for Filipino youth and women. Reflecting the mission of its partner organization, 
                                AU continues to spearhead initiatives centered on advocating for the rights and well-being of children 
                                while achieving a holistic society supported by equitable opportunities.
                                <br><br>
                                AU envisions a brighter future for the Filipino youth and women through integration of Lasallian values depicted 
                                in various charitable endeavors. An organization dedicated to making a difference that will sustain its 
                                objectives and goals in hopes of achieving a holistic society that will prioritize the rights of the people.
                            </p>
                        </div>

                        <div class="org-section">
                            <h2>Organization History</h2>
                            <p>
                            Archers for UNICEF (AU) was officially accredited by De La Salle University in 2017. At the time, only a few universities 
                            in the country — such as the University of the Philippines, University of Santo Tomas, and Ateneo de Manila University — 
                            had student organizations that worked closely with UNICEF. Seeing this gap within DLSU, then-sophomore Danielle Solancho 
                            recognized the need for an organization that could represent both the University's values and UNICEF's mission.
                            <br><br>
                            Driven by her long-standing involvement in student organizations and her passion for service, Danielle actively sought 
                            opportunities to volunteer beyond the University. She reached out to various non-profit organizations, including UNICEF, 
                            hoping to gain experience and contribute meaningfully. However, these efforts were often met with rejection or no response 
                            at all. Rather than discouraging her, these setbacks highlighted the lack of accessible avenues for students who genuinely 
                            wanted to serve.
                            <br><br>
                            When the opportunity to establish a new organization in DLSU arose, Danielle took it as a sign to move forward. With careful 
                            planning, extensive paperwork, and the support of her family, she began laying the foundation for Archers for UNICEF. After 
                            a series of discussions and coordination, UNICEF eventually agreed to partner with DLSU, marking the official beginning of AU. 
                            Since then, the organization has grown into a space where students can actively engage in advocacy, give back to marginalized 
                            communities, and take part in initiatives that aim to create meaningful and lasting impact.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <aside class="org-aside">
                        <div class="org-section">
                            <h2>Current Board</h2>
                            <div class="board-cards">

                                <div class="board-card">
                                    <h4>Cherubim Citco</h4>
                                    <span>President</span>
                                </div>

                                <div class="board-card">
                                    <h4>Aiella Evangelista</h4>
                                    <span>EVP - Internal Affairs</span>
                                </div>

                                <div class="board-card">
                                    <h4>Grace Gonzales</h4>
                                    <span>EVP - External Affairs</span>
                                </div>

                                <div class="board-card">
                                    <h4>Karll Cueto</h4>
                                    <span>EVP - Integrated Marketing Communications</span>
                                </div>

                                <div class="board-card">
                                    <h4>Aryanna Infante</h4>
                                    <span>EVP - Operations</span>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </aside>

                </div>
                
                <button id="create-post-btn" class="create-post hidden"> Create Post </button>

                <div class="org-posts">
                    <% if (posts && posts.length > 0) { %>
                        <% posts.forEach(function(post) { %>
                            <article class="org-post" id="post-<%= post._id %>">
                                <% if (post.image) { %>
                                <img src="<%= post.image %>"
                                    alt="<%= post.title %>"
                                    class="post-image lightbox-trigger">
                                <% } %>

                                <div class="post-header">
                                    <h3><%= post.title %></h3>
                                    <div class="post-actions" style="display: flex; gap: 10px; align-items: center;">
                                        <!-- LIKE BUTTON - FOR ALL LOGGED IN USERS -->
                                        <% if (user) { %>
                                            <% 
                                                let userLiked = false;
                                                if (post.likes) {
                                                    userLiked = post.likes.some(function(like) {
                                                        return like.toString() === user.id.toString();
                                                    });
                                                }
                                            %>
                                            <button class="like-btn" 
                                                    data-post-id="<%= post._id %>"
                                                    data-liked-by-user="<%= userLiked %>"
                                                    style="display: inline-flex; align-items: center; gap: 5px; background: none; border: 1px solid #046307; padding: 5px 10px; border-radius: 20px; color: #046307; cursor: pointer;">
                                                ❤️ <span class="like-count"><%= post.likes ? post.likes.length : 0 %></span>
                                            </button>
                                        <% } %>
                                        
                                        <!-- EDIT/DELETE BUTTONS - ONLY FOR ORG OWNER -->
                                        <% if (user && user.userType === 'organization' && user.email === 'au@dlsu.edu.ph') { %>
                                            <button class="edit-post-btn" onclick="showEditPostModal('<%= post._id %>')" style="background: none; border: 1px solid #046307; color: #046307; padding: 5px 10px; border-radius: 4px; cursor: pointer;">Edit</button>
                                            <form action="/posts/delete/<%= post._id %>" method="POST" style="display: inline;">
                                                <input type="hidden" name="orgName" value="Archers for UNICEF">
                                                <button type="submit" class="delete-post-btn" onclick="return confirm('Are you sure?')" style="background: none; border: 1px solid #046307; color: #046307; padding: 5px 10px; border-radius: 4px; cursor: pointer;">Delete</button>
                                            </form>
                                        <% } %>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                
                                <span class="post-date"><%= new Date(post.createdAt).toLocaleDateString('en-US', { year: 'numeric', month: 'long', day: 'numeric' }) %></span>
                                
                                <div class="post-content">
                                    <%- post.content.replace(/\n/g, '<br>') %>
                                </div>

                                <button class="comment-toggle">View comments</button>
                                <div class="comments hidden">
                                    <% 
                                        // Filter comments for this post
                                        var postComments = [];
                                        if (comments && comments.length > 0) {
                                            postComments = comments.filter(function(c) { 
                                                return c.post && c.post.toString() === post._id.toString(); 
                                            });
                                        }
                                    %>
                                    
                                    <% if (postComments.length > 0) { %>
                                        <% postComments.forEach(function(comment) { %>
                                            <div class="comment" data-owner="<%= comment.user ? comment.user._id : '' %>">
                                                <div class="comment-header">
                                                    <strong>
                                                        <% if (comment.user) { %>
                                                            <% if (comment.user.userType === "admin") { %>
                                                                Admin
                                                            <% } else if (comment.user.userType === "organization") { %>
                                                                <%= comment.user.orgName %>
                                                            <% } else { %>
                                                                <%= comment.user.firstName %> <%= comment.user.lastName %>
                                                            <% } %>
                                                        <% } else { %>
                                                            User
                                                        <% } %>
                                                    </strong>
                                                    
                                                    <% if (user && (user.userType === "admin" || (comment.user && comment.user._id.toString() === user.id.toString()))) { %>
                                                        <div class="comment-actions">
                                                            <button class="edit-comment-btn">Edit</button>
                                                            <form action="/delete-comment/<%= comment._id %>" method="POST" style="display: inline;">
                                                                <button type="submit" class="delete-comment-btn">Delete</button>
                                                            </form>
                                                        </div>
                                                    <% } %>
                                                </div>
                                                
                                                <p class="comment-text"><%= comment.text %></p>
                                                
                                                <form action="/edit-comment/<%= comment._id %>" method="POST" class="edit-comment-form hidden">
                                                    <input type="text" name="text" value="<%= comment.text %>" required>
                                                    <button type="submit">Save</button>
                                                </form>
                                            </div>
                                        <% }); %>
                                    <% } else { %>
                                        <p>No comments yet.</p>
                                    <% } %>

                                    <% if (user) { %>
                                        <form action="/add-comment" method="POST" class="add-comment">
                                            <textarea name="text" class="comment-input" placeholder="Write a comment..."></textarea>
                                            <input type="hidden" name="page" value="org1">
                                            <input type="hidden" name="postId" value="<%= post._id %>">
                                            <button type="submit" class="submit-comment">Post</button>
                                        </form>
                                    <% } else { %>
                                        <p class="login-warning"><a href="/login">Log in</a> to add a comment.</p>
                                    <% } %>
                                </div>
                            </article>
                        <% }); %>
                    <% } else { %>
                        <p class="no-posts">No posts yet.</p>
                    <% } %>
                </div>
            </section>
        </main>

        <div id="create-post-modal" class="modal hidden">
            <div class="modal-content">
                <h3>Create New Post</h3>
                
                <input type="text" id="new-post-title" placeholder="Post title">
                
                <textarea id="new-post-content" placeholder="Write your announcement..."></textarea>
                
                <!-- Image selection area -->
                <div class="image-selection-area">
                    <button type="button" id="select-image-btn" class="btn-secondary">Choose Image</button>
                    <span id="selected-image-name">No image selected</span>
                    <input type="hidden" id="new-post-image" value="">
                </div>
                
                <!-- Image preview -->
                <div id="image-preview" style="display: none; margin-top: 10px;">
                    <img src="" alt="Preview" style="max-width: 100%; max-height: 200px; border-radius: 8px;">
                    <button type="button" id="remove-image-btn" class="btn-small" style="margin-top: 5px;">Remove</button>
                </div>
                
                <div class="modal-actions">
                    <button id="submit-post">Post</button>
                    <button id="cancel-post">Cancel</button>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Edit Post Modal -->
        <div id="edit-post-modal" class="modal hidden">
            <div class="modal-content">
                <h3>Edit Post</h3>
                <form action="" method="POST" id="edit-post-form">
                    <input type="hidden" name="orgName" value="Archers for UNICEF">
                    
                    <div class="form-group">
                        <label for="edit-title">Title:</label>
                        <input type="text" name="title" id="edit-title" required>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="form-group">
                        <label for="edit-content">Content:</label>
                        <textarea name="content" id="edit-content" rows="6" required></textarea>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="form-group">
                        <label for="edit-image">Image URL:</label>
                        <input type="text" name="image" id="edit-image" placeholder="/assets/post-image.jpg">
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="modal-actions">
                        <button type="submit" class="btn-primary">Save Changes</button>
                        <button type="button" id="cancel-edit" class="btn-secondary">Cancel</button>
                    </div>
                </form>
            </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Image Selector Modal -->
        <div id="image-selector-modal" class="modal hidden">
            <div class="modal-content" style="max-width: 800px;">
                <h3>Select an Image</h3>
                
                <div class="image-grid" style="display: grid; grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr); gap: 15px; margin: 20px 0; max-height: 400px; overflow-y: auto;">
                    <!-- Images will be loaded here dynamically -->
                </div>
                
                <div class="modal-actions">
                    <button type="button" id="close-image-selector" class="btn-secondary">Cancel</button>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>


        <div id="js-lightbox" class="js-lightbox hidden">
            <span class="js-lightbox-close">&times;</span>
            <img src="" alt="Expanded view">
        </div>

        <script src="/script.js"></script>
        
    </body>
</html>